==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impolitic
<hw>Im*pol"i*tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>politic</ets>; cf. F.
<ets>impolitique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not politic; contrary to, or wanting
in, policy; unwise; imprudent; indiscreet; inexpedient; <as>as, an
<ex>impolitic</ex> ruler, law, or measure</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The most unjust and <qex>impolitic</qex> of all things, unequal
taxation.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Indiscreet; inexpedient; undiplomatic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 737 --></p>

<p><ent>Impolitical</ent>⟦br⟧
